Autoboxing is the automatic conversion that Java compiler makes between primitive types and their corresponding
object wrapper classes. Example, converting int -> Integer, double -> Double... If the conversion goes the other way,
this is called unboxing. Typically, this is used in Collections that cannot hold other than Objects, where boxing
primitive types is needed before setting them in the collection.
