Section 126.15: Using ThreadLocal
A useful tool in Java Concurrency is ThreadLocal – this allows you to have a variable that will be unique to a given
thread. Thus, if the same code runs in different threads, these executions will not share the value, but instead each
thread has its own variable that is local to the thread.
